Gatundu South MP Moses Kuria has been charged at a Milimani court with assault and causing bodily harm. He is said to have unlawfully assaulted Joyce Wanja Gacoe at Royal Media Services offices in Kilimani on December 8, 2019. He has pleaded not guilty to the charges and through Senior Counsel John Khaminwa, asked for affordable bail and bond terms. Chief magistrate Martha Mutuku has released Kuria on a Sh50,000 bond with an alternative cash bail of Sh20,000. The case will be mentioned on February 8. More to follow...